Adhere to the following principles:
- Logos: Logos must maintain minimum dimensions and safe areas as per the guidelines. Use the following logo variants:
    - Transparent background, "sports" text in mint color: https://dumpster.cdn.sports.ru/e/01/b6a5c8d6223d46030fe91d0aa70cc.png
    - Mint background, "sports" text in black: https://dumpster.cdn.sports.ru/0/08/cc55d04e9b8982897827dccb94e8f.png
    - Black background, "sports" text in mint: https://dumpster.cdn.sports.ru/2/d2/0266f2830fbca50f821147bc0c010.png
- Typography: Style headings with the "Sports" font (e.g., 40px, 32px, 24px) and use the "Roboto" or Neoris font family for the main text.
- Patterns and Pictograms: Use branded patterns (both static and dynamic) and pictograms designed on a 20×20 px grid to create accent elements.
- Layout: The layout should follow a modular grid with clearly defined columns, margins, and safe areas to ensure compositional balance.
- Branded Colors: Apply the branded colors (for example, using var(--sports-primary-color) for accents, var(--sports-primary-color-hover) for interactive elements, and var(--sports-black) for texts) to maintain the style’s recognizability.
- Goal: Create a website that visually conveys the dynamic energy of sports, emphasizes the professionalism of the Sports brand, and features a modern, clean, and technologically advanced interface.

